{"lemma": "قادِرٌ", "slug": "قادِرٌ", "root": "ق.د.ر", "root_slug": "ق-د-ر", "root_link": "/words/roots/ق-د-ر", "pos": "ADJ", "pos_camel": "adj", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "قادِر", "root": "قدر", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 14}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 2, "pos_tags": ["adj", "name"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 4}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n35294"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "powerful", "fa": "توانا", "ur": "قادر", "tr": "kadir", "id": "maha kuasa", "bn": "শক্তিমান", "es": "poderoso", "fr": "puissant", "de": "mächtig", "ru": "могущественный", "zh": "全能的"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "adj", "gloss": "powerful"}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "capable, able", "examples": [{"text": "إن القلب الذي لم يعد قادرًا على الشعور بالرحمة لا يمكن أن يكون وعاءً للخلاص أو وعاءً للإيمان الحقيقي.", "english": "A heart that is no longer capable of feeling compassion cannot be a vessel of salvation or a vessel of true faith."}, {"text": "هل تعتقد أن الكتاب المقدس قادر أن يخبرنا عن المستقبل؟", "english": "Do you think the Bible can tell us about the future?"}]}, {"pos": "adj", "gloss": "efficient, talented"}, {"pos": "name", "gloss": "one of God's names in Islam, (\"the All Able, the Powerful, the Omnipotent\")"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Derived from the active participle of the verb قَدَرَ (qadara)."}, "ipa": ["/qaː.dir/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n35294", "headword_ar": "قَادِرٌ", "root": "qdr", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", applied to God,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muqad~irN", "text_ar": "مُقَدِّرٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Decreeing, appointing, ordaining, deciding"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (S;) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qadiyrN", "text_ar": "قَدِيرٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "may signify the same. (TA.)       -A2-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qadorN", "text_ar": "قَدْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", last signification.       -A3-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Possessing power,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ability;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qadiyrN", "text_ar": "قَدِيرٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muqotadirN", "text_ar": "مُقْتَدِرٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (TA:) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qadiyrN", "text_ar": "قَدِيرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "has an intensive signification, and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muqotadirN", "text_ar": "مُقْتَدِرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "still more so: (IAth:) or ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qadiyrN", "text_ar": "قَدِيرٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies he"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "who does what he will, according to what wisdom requires, not more nor less;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and therefore this epithet is applied to none but God; and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "muqotadirN", "text_ar": "مُقْتَدِرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies nearly the same, but is sometimes applied to a human being, and means one"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "who applies himself, as to a task, to acquire power or ability."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(El-Basáïr.) When you say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Aall~`hu EalaY kul~i $aYo'K", "text_ar": "اَللّٰهُ عَلَى كُلِّ شَىْءٍ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qadiyrN", "text_ar": "قَدِيرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "God is able to do everything; is omnipotent;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] you mean, to do everything that is possible. (Msb.) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bayona A^aroDika waA^aroDi fulaAnK layolapN qaAdirapN", "text_ar": "بَيْنَ اَرْضِكَ وَاَرْضِ فُلَانٍ لَيْلَةٌ قَادِرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Yaakoob, S;) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bayonanaA lylyp qAdrp", "text_ar": "بَيْنَنَا ليلية قادرة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (K;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Between thy land and the land of such a one is a gentle night's journey;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Yaakoob, S;) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "between us is an easy night's journey, in which is no fatigue."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K.)       -A4-  See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qadiyrN", "text_ar": "قَدِيرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "."}], "source_refs": ["K", "TA", "IAth"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}